Instead of writing:
Example
int time = 20;
if (time < 18) {
printf("Good day.");
} else {
printf("Good evening.");
}

You can simply write:
Example
int time = 20;
(time < 18) ? printf("Good day.") : printf("Good evening.");

It is completely up to you if you want to use the traditional if...else statement or the ternary operator.

